  "title": "Assistant Professor",
  "department": "School of Social Science",
  "school": "",
  "profile_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/faculty/bikash-ch-bhowmick",
  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/Bikash-C-Bhowmick.jpg?itok=ui_oWFCm",
  "bio_raw": "He is currently teaching in the Media Studies and Journalism Department of the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB). He has taught at Stamford University, Bangladesh.\nHe did his Postgraduate Diploma in Cultural Studies in 2009 at the Centre for the Study of Culture and Society (CSCS), Bangalore, India. He completed his MA degree in Film and Media from Stamford University, Bangladesh and BSc in Statistics from University of Dhaka.\nHe has received a CSCS PhD Coursework Fellowship for the year 2009 and a Bangladesh Film Archive Research Fellowship for 2008. He published four books: Women on Screen (2009), Jhora Patar Galpo (From the Pages of Memory, a fiction novel, 2010), Chalochchittrey Galpo Bola (Film Storytelling, 2014) and Porichoyheena (fiction novel, 2016). He also directed a film Matir Tane (Turn to the Root, 2005) with Anwar Chowdhury, which was screened at the ‘Documentary Film Festival 2007’ in Dhaka.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Women and Cinema, Screenplay Writing and Analysis, Reception, Audience and Fan Studies, Star Studies, Community Radio, Screenwriting Research, Audience and Fan Studies."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nDoctoral Researcher\n, University of Malaya (UM), Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia\nPostgraduate Diploma in Cultural Studies\n, Centre for the Study of Culture and Society (CSCS), Bangalore, India.\nMA in Film and Media\n, Stamford University Bangladesh.\nBSc in Statistics\n, University of Dhaka."
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
